summary.p: General options for all series types.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.AllowPointSelect
member.summary: Allow this series' points to be selected by clicking on the markers or bars.

summary.p: Enable or disable the initial animation when a series is displayed. The animation can also be set as a configuration object. Please note that this option only applies to the initial animation of the series itself. For other animations, see chart.animation and the animation parameter under the API methods.The following properties are supported:

dl.dd: The duration of the animation in milliseconds.

When using jQuery as the general framework, the easing can be set to linear orswing. More easing functions are available with the use of jQuery plug-ins, most notablythe jQuery UI suite. See the jQuery docs. When using MooTools as the general framework, use the property name transition instead of easing.

summary.p: Due to poor performance, animation is disabled in old IE browsers for column charts and polar charts.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Color
member.summary: The main color of the series. In line type series it applies to the line and the point markers unless otherwise specified. In bar type series it applies to the bars unless a color is specified per point. The default value is pulled from the options.colors array.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Compare
member.summary: Compare the values of the series against the first value in the visible range. The y axis will show percentage or absolute change depending on whether compare is set to "percent" or "value". When this is applied to multiple series, it allows comparing the development of the series against each other.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.ConnectNulls
member.summary: Whether to draw a line between points on either side of a null point, or render a gap between them.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.CropThreshold
member.summary: When the series contains less points than the crop threshold, all points are drawn, event if the points fall outside the visible plot area at the current zoom. The advantage of drawing all points (including markers and columns), is that animation is performed on updates. On the other hand, when the series contains more points than the crop threshold, the series data is cropped to only contain points that fall within the plot area. The advantage of cropping away invisible points is to increase performance on large series. .

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Cursor
member.summary: You can set the cursor to "pointer" if you have click events attached to the series, to signal to the user that the points and lines can be clicked.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.DashStyle
member.summary:
A name for the dash style to use for the graph. Applies only to series type having a graph, like line, spline, area and scatter in case it has a lineWidth. The value for the dashStyle include:
Solid
ShortDash
ShortDot
ShortDashDot
ShortDashDotDot
Dot
Dash
LongDash
DashDot
LongDashDot
LongDashDotDot

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.EnableMouseTracking
member.summary: Enable or disable the mouse tracking for a specific series. This includes point tooltips and click events on graphs and points. When using shared tooltips (default in stock charts), mouse tracking is not required. For large datasets it improves performance.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.FillColor
member.summary: Fill color or gradient for the area. When null, the series' color is used with the series' fillOpacity.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.FillOpacity
member.summary: Fill opacity for the area. Note that when you set an explicit fillColor, the fillOpacity is not applied. Instead, you should define the opacity in the fillColor with an rgba color definition.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.GapSize
member.summary:
Defines when to display a gap in the graph. A gap size of 5 means that if the distance between two points is greater than five times that of the two closest points, the graph will be broken.
In practice, this option is most often used to visualize gaps in time series. In a stock chart, intraday data is available for daytime hours, while gaps will appear in nights and weekends..

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Keys
member.summary: An array specifying which option maps to which key in the data point array. This makes it convenient to work with unstructured data arrays from different sources.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.LegendIndex
member.summary: The sequential index of the series within the legend.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.LineColor
member.summary: A separate color for the graph line. By default the line takes the color of the series, but the lineColor setting allows setting a separate color for the line without altering the fillColor.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.LineWidth
member.summary: Pixel with of the graph line.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.LinkedTo
member.summary: The id of another series to link to. Additionally, the value can be ":previous" to link to the previous series. When two series are linked, only the first one appears in the legend. Toggling the visibility of this also toggles the linked series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Point
member.summary: Properties for each single point

summary.p: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointInterval defines the interval of the x values in milliseconds. For example, if a series contains one value each day, set pointInterval to 24 * 3600 * 1000.
Since Highstock 2.1, it can be combined with pointIntervalUnit to draw irregular intervals.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.PointIntervalUnit
member.summary: On datetime series, this allows for setting the pointInterval to the two irregular time units, month and year. Combine it with pointInterval to draw quarters, 6 months, 10 years etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.PointRange
member.summary: The width of each point on the x axis. For example in a column chart with one value each day, the pointRange would be 1 day (= 24 * 3600 * 1000 milliseconds). This is normally computed automatically, but this option can be used to override the automatic value.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.PointStart
member.summary: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointStart defines on what value to start. On a datetime X axis, the number will be given as milliseconds since 1970-01-01, for example Date.UTC(2011, 0, 1).

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Selected
member.summary: Whether to select the series initially. If showCheckbox is true, the checkbox next to the series name in the legend will be checked for a selected series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Shadow
member.summary: Whether to apply a drop shadow to the graph line. Since 1.1.7 the shadow can be an object configuration containing color, offsetX, offsetY, opacity and width.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.ShowCheckbox
member.summary: If true, a checkbox is displayed next to the legend item to allow selecting the series. The state of the checkbox is determined by the selected option.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.ShowInLegend
member.summary: Whether to display this particular series or series type in the legend. The default value is true for standalone series, false for linked series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Stacking
member.summary: Whether to stack the values of each series on top of each other. Possible values are null to disable, "normal" to stack by value or "percent".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.States
member.summary: A wrapper object for all the series options in specific states.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.StickyTracking
member.summary: Sticky tracking of mouse events. When true, the mouseOut event on a series isn't triggered until the mouse moves over another series, or out of the plot area. When false, the mouseOut event on a series is triggered when the mouse leaves the area around the series' graph or markers. This also implies the tooltip when not shared. When stickyTracking is false, the tooltip will be hidden when moving the mouse between series. Defaults to true for line and area type series, but to false for columns, candlesticks etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Threshold
member.summary: The Y axis value to serve as the base for the area, for distinguishing between values above and below a threshold. If null, the area behaves like a line series with fill between the graph and the Y axis minimum.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Tooltip
member.summary: A configuration object for the tooltip rendering of each single series. Properties are inherited from tooltip, but only the following properties can be defined on a series level.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.TrackByArea
member.summary: Whether the whole area or just the line should respond to mouseover tooltips and other mouse or touch events.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.TurboThreshold
member.summary: When a series contains a data array that is longer than this, only one dimensional arrays of numbers, or two dimensional arrays with x and y values are allowed. Also, only the first point is tested, and the rest are assumed to be the same format. This saves expensive data checking and indexing in long series. Set it to 0 disable.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArea.Visible
member.summary: Set the initial visibility of the series.

member.summary: An array defining zones within a series.

summary.p: Datetime formats for the header of the tooltip in a stock chart. The format can vary within a chart depending on the currently selected time range and the current data grouping.
The default formats are:

For each of these array definitions, the first item is the format used when the active time span is one unit. For instance, if the current data applies to one week, the first item of the week array is used. The second and third items are used when the active time span is more than two units. For instance, if the current data applies to two weeks, the second and third item of the week array are used, and applied to the start and end date of the time span.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataGrouping.Enabled
member.summary: Enable or disable data grouping. Defaults to true.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataGrouping.Forced
member.summary: When data grouping is forced, it runs no matter how small the intervals are. This can be handy for example when the sum should be calculated for values appearing at random times within each hour. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataGrouping.GroupPixelWidth
member.summary: The approximate pixel width of each group. If for example a series with 30 points is displayed over a 600 pixel wide plot area, no grouping is performed. If however the series contains so many points that the spacing is less than the groupPixelWidth, Highcharts will try to group it into appropriate groups so that each is more or less two pixels wide. If multiple series with different group pixel widths are drawn on the same x axis, all series will take the greatest width. For example, line series have 2px default group width, while column series have 10px. If combined, both the line and the column will have 10px by default. Defaults to 2.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataGrouping.Smoothed
member.summary: Normally, a group is indexed by the start of that group, so for example when 30 daily values are grouped into one month, that month's x value will be the 1st of the month. This apparently shifts the data to the left. When the smoothed option is true, this is compensated for. The data is shifted to the middle of the group, and min and max values are preserved. Internally, this is used in the Navigator series. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Align
member.summary: The alignment of the data label compared to the point. If right, the right side of the label should be touching the point. For points with an extent, like columns, the alignments also dictates how to align it inside the box, as given with the inside option. Can be one of "left", "center" or "right".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.AllowOverlap
member.summary: Whether to allow data labels to overlap. To make the labels less sensitive for overlapping, the dataLabels.padding can be set to 0.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.BorderColor
member.summary: The border color for the data label. Defaults to undefined.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.BorderRadius
member.summary: The border radius in pixels for the data label.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.BorderWidth
member.summary: The border width in pixels for the data label.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Color
member.summary: The text color for the data labels. Defaults to null.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Crop
member.summary: Whether to hide data labels that are outside the plot area. By default, the data label is moved inside the plot area according to the overflow option.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Defer
member.summary: Whether to defer displaying the data labels until the initial series animation has finished.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Enabled
member.summary: Enable or disable the data labels.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Format
member.summary: A format string for the data label. Available variables are the same as for formatter.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Formatter
member.summary:
Callback JavaScript function to format the data label. Note that if a format is defined, the format takes precedence and the formatter is ignored. Available data are:
this.percentage Stacked series and pies only. The point's percentage of the total.
this.point The point object. The point name, if defined, is available through this.point.name.
this.series: The series object. The series name is available through this.series.name.
this.total Stacked series only. The total value at this point's x value.
this.x: The x value.
this.y: The y value.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Inside
member.summary: For points with an extent, like columns, whether to align the data label inside the box or to the actual value point. Defaults to false in most cases, true in stacked columns.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Overflow
member.summary: How to handle data labels that flow outside the plot area. The default is justify, which aligns them inside the plot area. For columns and bars, this means it will be moved inside the bar. To display data labels outside the plot area, set crop to false and overflow to "none".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaDataLabels.Padding
member.summary: When either the borderWidth or the backgroundColor is set, this is the padding within the box.

summary.p: A predefined shape or symbol for the marker. When null, the symbol is pulled from options.symbols. Other possible values are "circle", "square", "diamond", "triangle" and "triangle-down".
Additionally, the URL to a graphic can be given on this form: "url(graphic.png)". Note that for the image to be applied to exported charts, its URL needs to be accessible by the export server.
Custom callbacks for symbol path generation can also be added to Highcharts.SVGRenderer.prototype.symbols. The callback is then used by its method name, as shown in the demo.

member.summary: Allow this series' points to be selected by clicking on the markers or bars.

summary.p: Enable or disable the initial animation when a series is displayed. The animation can also be set as a configuration object. Please note that this option only applies to the initial animation of the series itself. For other animations, see chart.animation and the animation parameter under the API methods.The following properties are supported:

dl.dd: The duration of the animation in milliseconds.

When using jQuery as the general framework, the easing can be set to linear orswing. More easing functions are available with the use of jQuery plug-ins, most notablythe jQuery UI suite. See the jQuery docs. When using MooTools as the general framework, use the property name transition instead of easing.

summary.p: Due to poor performance, animation is disabled in old IE browsers for column charts and polar charts.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.Color
member.summary: The main color of the series. In line type series it applies to the line and the point markers unless otherwise specified. In bar type series it applies to the bars unless a color is specified per point. The default value is pulled from the options.colors array.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.Compare
member.summary: Compare the values of the series against the first value in the visible range. The y axis will show percentage or absolute change depending on whether compare is set to "percent" or "value". When this is applied to multiple series, it allows comparing the development of the series against each other.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.ConnectNulls
member.summary: Whether to draw a line between points on either side of a null point, or render a gap between them.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.CropThreshold
member.summary: When the series contains less points than the crop threshold, all points are drawn, event if the points fall outside the visible plot area at the current zoom. The advantage of drawing all points (including markers and columns), is that animation is performed on updates. On the other hand, when the series contains more points than the crop threshold, the series data is cropped to only contain points that fall within the plot area. The advantage of cropping away invisible points is to increase performance on large series. .

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.Cursor
member.summary: You can set the cursor to "pointer" if you have click events attached to the series, to signal to the user that the points and lines can be clicked.

member.summary: Extended data labels for range series types. Range series data labels have no x and y options. Instead, they have xLow, xHigh, yLow and yHigh options to allow the higher and lower data label sets individually.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.EnableMouseTracking
member.summary: Enable or disable the mouse tracking for a specific series. This includes point tooltips and click events on graphs and points. When using shared tooltips (default in stock charts), mouse tracking is not required. For large datasets it improves performance.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.FillColor
member.summary: Fill color or gradient for the area. When null, the series' color is used with the series' fillOpacity.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.FillOpacity
member.summary: Fill opacity for the area. Note that when you set an explicit fillColor, the fillOpacity is not applied. Instead, you should define the opacity in the fillColor with an rgba color definition.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.GapSize
member.summary:
Defines when to display a gap in the graph. A gap size of 5 means that if the distance between two points is greater than five times that of the two closest points, the graph will be broken.
In practice, this option is most often used to visualize gaps in time series. In a stock chart, intraday data is available for daytime hours, while gaps will appear in nights and weekends..

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.Keys
member.summary: An array specifying which option maps to which key in the data point array. This makes it convenient to work with unstructured data arrays from different sources.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.LegendIndex

member.summary: A separate color for the graph line. By default the line takes the color of the series, but the lineColor setting allows setting a separate color for the line without altering the fillColor.

member.summary: The id of another series to link to. Additionally, the value can be ":previous" to link to the previous series. When two series are linked, only the first one appears in the legend. Toggling the visibility of this also toggles the linked series.

member.summary: Properties for each single point

summary.p: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointInterval defines the interval of the x values in milliseconds. For example, if a series contains one value each day, set pointInterval to 24 * 3600 * 1000.
Since Highstock 2.1, it can be combined with pointIntervalUnit to draw irregular intervals.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.PointIntervalUnit
member.summary: On datetime series, this allows for setting the pointInterval to the two irregular time units, month and year. Combine it with pointInterval to draw quarters, 6 months, 10 years etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.PointRange
member.summary: The width of each point on the x axis. For example in a column chart with one value each day, the pointRange would be 1 day (= 24 * 3600 * 1000 milliseconds). This is normally computed automatically, but this option can be used to override the automatic value.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.PointStart
member.summary: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointStart defines on what value to start. On a datetime X axis, the number will be given as milliseconds since 1970-01-01, for example Date.UTC(2011, 0, 1).

member.summary: Whether to stack the values of each series on top of each other. Possible values are null to disable, "normal" to stack by value or "percent".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearange.StickyTracking
member.summary: Sticky tracking of mouse events. When true, the mouseOut event on a series isn't triggered until the mouse moves over another series, or out of the plot area. When false, the mouseOut event on a series is triggered when the mouse leaves the area around the series' graph or markers. This also implies the tooltip when not shared. When stickyTracking is false, the tooltip will be hidden when moving the mouse between series. Defaults to true for line and area type series, but to false for columns, candlesticks etc.

member.summary: When a series contains a data array that is longer than this, only one dimensional arrays of numbers, or two dimensional arrays with x and y values are allowed. Also, only the first point is tested, and the rest are assumed to be the same format. This saves expensive data checking and indexing in long series. Set it to 0 disable.

summary.p: Datetime formats for the header of the tooltip in a stock chart. The format can vary within a chart depending on the currently selected time range and the current data grouping.
The default formats are:

For each of these array definitions, the first item is the format used when the active time span is one unit. For instance, if the current data applies to one week, the first item of the week array is used. The second and third items are used when the active time span is more than two units. For instance, if the current data applies to two weeks, the second and third item of the week array are used, and applied to the start and end date of the time span.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeDataGrouping.Enabled
member.summary: Enable or disable data grouping. Defaults to true.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeDataGrouping.Forced
member.summary: When data grouping is forced, it runs no matter how small the intervals are. This can be handy for example when the sum should be calculated for values appearing at random times within each hour. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeDataGrouping.GroupPixelWidth
member.summary: The approximate pixel width of each group. If for example a series with 30 points is displayed over a 600 pixel wide plot area, no grouping is performed. If however the series contains so many points that the spacing is less than the groupPixelWidth, Highcharts will try to group it into appropriate groups so that each is more or less two pixels wide. If multiple series with different group pixel widths are drawn on the same x axis, all series will take the greatest width. For example, line series have 2px default group width, while column series have 10px. If combined, both the line and the column will have 10px by default. Defaults to 2.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeDataGrouping.Smoothed
member.summary: Normally, a group is indexed by the start of that group, so for example when 30 daily values are grouped into one month, that month's x value will be the 1st of the month. This apparently shifts the data to the left. When the smoothed option is true, this is compensated for. The data is shifted to the middle of the group, and min and max values are preserved. Internally, this is used in the Navigator series. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeEvents.LegendItemClick
member.summary: Fires when the legend item belonging to the series is clicked. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. This contains common event information based on jQuery or MooTools depending on which library is used as the base for Highcharts. The default action is to toggle the visibility of the series. This can be prevented by returning false or calling event.preventDefault().

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeEvents.MouseOut
member.summary: Fires when the mouse leaves the graph. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. This contains common event information based on jQuery or MooTools depending on which library is used as the base for Highcharts. If the stickyTracking option is true, mouseOut doesn't happen before the mouse enters another graph or leaves the plot area.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeEvents.MouseOver
member.summary: Fires when the mouse enters the graph. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. This contains common event information based on jQuery or MooTools depending on which library is used as the base for Highcharts.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeEvents.Show
member.summary: Fires when the series is shown after chart generation time, either by clicking the legend item or by calling .show().

member.summary:
Fires when a point is clicked. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. This contains common event information based on jQuery or MooTools depending on which library is used as the base for Highcharts.
If the series.allowPointSelect option is true, the default action for the point's click event is to toggle the point's select state. Returning false cancels this action.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangePointEvents.MouseOut

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangePointEvents.MouseOver
member.summary: Fires when the mouse enters the area close to the point. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. This contains common event information based on jQuery or MooTools depending on which library is used as the base for Highcharts.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangePointEvents.Remove
member.summary: Fires when the point is removed using the .remove() method. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. Returning false cancels the operation.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangePointEvents.Select

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangePointEvents.Unselect

member.summary: Fires when the point is updated programmatically through the .update() method. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. The new point options can be accessed through event.options. Returning false cancels the operation.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStates.Hover
member.summary: Options for the hovered series

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHover.Enabled
member.summary: Enable separate styles for the hovered series to visualize that the user hovers either the series itself or the legend. Enabling it has a performance penalty as it requires that a second layer be drawn as a double buffer. This means twice as much graphics to draw for each plot, which can make a great difference for charts with a high number of series or points..

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHover.Halo
member.summary: Options for the halo appearing around the hovered point in line-type series as well as outside the hovered slice in pie charts. By default the halo is filled by the current point or series color with an opacity of 0.25. The halo can be disabled by setting the halo option to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHover.LineWidth
member.summary: Pixel with of the graph line.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHover.LineWidthPlus
member.summary: The additional line width for the graph of a hovered series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverHalo.Attributes
member.summary: A collection of SVG attributes to override the appearance of the halo, for example fill, stroke and stroke-width.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverHalo.Opacity
member.summary: Opacity for the halo unless a specific fill is overridden using the attributes setting. Note that Highcharts is only able to apply opacity to colors of hex or rgb(a) formats.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverHalo.Size
member.summary: The pixel size of the halo. For point markers this is the radius of the halo. For pie slices it is the width of the halo outside the slice. For bubbles it defaults to 5 and is the width of the halo outside the bubble.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverMarker.Enabled
member.summary: Enable or disable the point marker. If null, the markers are hidden when the data is dense, and shown for more widespread data points.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverMarker.FillColor
member.summary: The fill color of the point marker. When null, the series' or point's color is used.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverMarker.Height
member.summary: Image markers only. Set the image width explicitly. When using this option, a width must also be set.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverMarker.LineColor
member.summary: The color of the point marker's outline. When null, the series' or point's color is used.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverMarker.LineWidth
member.summary: The width of the point marker's outline.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverMarker.Radius
member.summary: The radius of the point marker.

summary.p: A predefined shape or symbol for the marker. When null, the symbol is pulled from options.symbols. Other possible values are "circle", "square", "diamond", "triangle" and "triangle-down".
Additionally, the URL to a graphic can be given on this form: "url(graphic.png)". Note that for the image to be applied to exported charts, its URL needs to be accessible by the export server.
Custom callbacks for symbol path generation can also be added to Highcharts.SVGRenderer.prototype.symbols. The callback is then used by its method name, as shown in the demo.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeStatesHoverMarker.Width
member.summary: Image markers only. Set the image width explicitly. When using this option, a height must also be set.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.ChangeDecimals
member.summary: How many decimals to show for the point.change value when the series.compare option is set. This is overridable in each series' tooltip options object. The default is to preserve all decimals.

summary.p: Whether the tooltip should follow the mouse as it moves across columns, pie slices and other point types with an extent. By default it behaves this way for scatter, bubble and pie series by override in the plotOptions for those series types.
For touch moves to behave the same way, followTouchMove must be true also.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.FollowTouchMove
member.summary: Whether the tooltip should follow the finger as it moves on a touch device. In order to take effect, chart.zoomType and chart.pinchType must be disabled.

summary.p: The HTML of the tooltip header line. Variables are enclosed by curly brackets. Available variablesare point.key, series.name, series.color and other members from the point and series objects. The point.key variable contains the category name, x value or datetime string depending on the type of axis. For datetime axes, the point.key date format can be set using tooltip.xDateFormat.
Defaults to {point.key}

The HTML of the point's line in the tooltip. Variables are enclosed by curly brackets. Available variables are point.x, point.y, point.change, series.name and series.color and other properties on the same form. Furthermore, point.y can be extended by the tooltip.valuePrefix and tooltip.valueSuffix variables. This can also be overridden for each series, which makes it a good hook for displaying units.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.PointFormatter
member.summary: A callback function for formatting the HTML output for a single point in the tooltip. Like the pointFormat string, but with more flexibility.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.Shape
member.summary: The name of a symbol to use for the border around the tooltip. In Highstock 1.x, the shape was square.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.ValueDecimals
member.summary: How many decimals to show in each series' y value. This is overridable in each series' tooltip options object. The default is to preserve all decimals.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.ValuePrefix
member.summary: A string to prepend to each series' y value. Overridable in each series' tooltip options object.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.ValueSuffix
member.summary: A string to append to each series' y value. Overridable in each series' tooltip options object.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsArearangeTooltip.XDateFormat
member.summary: The format for the date in the tooltip header. If data grouping is used, the default is a smart guess based on how close the closest points are. It is pulled from the #plotOptions.dataGrouping.dateTimeLabelFormats array.

member.summary: Defines the color of the series.

member.summary: A name for the dash style to use for the graph.

member.summary: Defines the fill color for the series (in area type series)

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.AllowPointSelect
member.summary: Allow this series' points to be selected by clicking on the markers or bars.

summary.p: Enable or disable the initial animation when a series is displayed. The animation can also be set as a configuration object. Please note that this option only applies to the initial animation of the series itself. For other animations, see chart.animation and the animation parameter under the API methods.The following properties are supported:

dl.dd: The duration of the animation in milliseconds.

When using jQuery as the general framework, the easing can be set to linear orswing. More easing functions are available with the use of jQuery plug-ins, most notablythe jQuery UI suite. See the jQuery docs. When using MooTools as the general framework, use the property name transition instead of easing.

summary.p: Due to poor performance, animation is disabled in old IE browsers for column charts and polar charts.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Color
member.summary: The main color of the series. In line type series it applies to the line and the point markers unless otherwise specified. In bar type series it applies to the bars unless a color is specified per point. The default value is pulled from the options.colors array.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Compare
member.summary: Compare the values of the series against the first value in the visible range. The y axis will show percentage or absolute change depending on whether compare is set to "percent" or "value". When this is applied to multiple series, it allows comparing the development of the series against each other.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.ConnectNulls
member.summary: Whether to draw a line between points on either side of a null point, or render a gap between them.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.CropThreshold
member.summary: When the series contains less points than the crop threshold, all points are drawn, event if the points fall outside the visible plot area at the current zoom. The advantage of drawing all points (including markers and columns), is that animation is performed on updates. On the other hand, when the series contains more points than the crop threshold, the series data is cropped to only contain points that fall within the plot area. The advantage of cropping away invisible points is to increase performance on large series. .

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Cursor
member.summary: You can set the cursor to "pointer" if you have click events attached to the series, to signal to the user that the points and lines can be clicked.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.DashStyle
member.summary:
A name for the dash style to use for the graph. Applies only to series type having a graph, like line, spline, area and scatter in case it has a lineWidth. The value for the dashStyle include:
Solid
ShortDash
ShortDot
ShortDashDot
ShortDashDotDot
Dot
Dash
LongDash
DashDot
LongDashDot
LongDashDotDot

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.EnableMouseTracking
member.summary: Enable or disable the mouse tracking for a specific series. This includes point tooltips and click events on graphs and points. When using shared tooltips (default in stock charts), mouse tracking is not required. For large datasets it improves performance.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.FillColor
member.summary: Fill color or gradient for the area. When null, the series' color is used with the series' fillOpacity.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.FillOpacity
member.summary: Fill opacity for the area. Note that when you set an explicit fillColor, the fillOpacity is not applied. Instead, you should define the opacity in the fillColor with an rgba color definition.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.GapSize
member.summary:
Defines when to display a gap in the graph. A gap size of 5 means that if the distance between two points is greater than five times that of the two closest points, the graph will be broken.
In practice, this option is most often used to visualize gaps in time series. In a stock chart, intraday data is available for daytime hours, while gaps will appear in nights and weekends..

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Keys
member.summary: An array specifying which option maps to which key in the data point array. This makes it convenient to work with unstructured data arrays from different sources.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.LegendIndex
member.summary: The sequential index of the series within the legend.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.LineColor
member.summary: A separate color for the graph line. By default the line takes the color of the series, but the lineColor setting allows setting a separate color for the line without altering the fillColor.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.LineWidth
member.summary: Pixel with of the graph line.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.LinkedTo
member.summary: The id of another series to link to. Additionally, the value can be ":previous" to link to the previous series. When two series are linked, only the first one appears in the legend. Toggling the visibility of this also toggles the linked series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Point
member.summary: Properties for each single point

summary.p: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointInterval defines the interval of the x values in milliseconds. For example, if a series contains one value each day, set pointInterval to 24 * 3600 * 1000.
Since Highstock 2.1, it can be combined with pointIntervalUnit to draw irregular intervals.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.PointIntervalUnit
member.summary: On datetime series, this allows for setting the pointInterval to the two irregular time units, month and year. Combine it with pointInterval to draw quarters, 6 months, 10 years etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.PointRange
member.summary: The width of each point on the x axis. For example in a column chart with one value each day, the pointRange would be 1 day (= 24 * 3600 * 1000 milliseconds). This is normally computed automatically, but this option can be used to override the automatic value.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.PointStart
member.summary: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointStart defines on what value to start. On a datetime X axis, the number will be given as milliseconds since 1970-01-01, for example Date.UTC(2011, 0, 1).

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Selected
member.summary: Whether to select the series initially. If showCheckbox is true, the checkbox next to the series name in the legend will be checked for a selected series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Shadow
member.summary: Whether to apply a drop shadow to the graph line. Since 1.1.7 the shadow can be an object configuration containing color, offsetX, offsetY, opacity and width.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.ShowCheckbox
member.summary: If true, a checkbox is displayed next to the legend item to allow selecting the series. The state of the checkbox is determined by the selected option.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.ShowInLegend
member.summary: Whether to display this particular series or series type in the legend. The default value is true for standalone series, false for linked series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Stacking
member.summary: Whether to stack the values of each series on top of each other. Possible values are null to disable, "normal" to stack by value or "percent".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.States
member.summary: A wrapper object for all the series options in specific states.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.StickyTracking
member.summary: Sticky tracking of mouse events. When true, the mouseOut event on a series isn't triggered until the mouse moves over another series, or out of the plot area. When false, the mouseOut event on a series is triggered when the mouse leaves the area around the series' graph or markers. This also implies the tooltip when not shared. When stickyTracking is false, the tooltip will be hidden when moving the mouse between series. Defaults to true for line and area type series, but to false for columns, candlesticks etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Threshold
member.summary: The Y axis value to serve as the base for the area, for distinguishing between values above and below a threshold. If null, the area behaves like a line series with fill between the graph and the Y axis minimum.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Tooltip
member.summary: A configuration object for the tooltip rendering of each single series. Properties are inherited from tooltip, but only the following properties can be defined on a series level.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.TrackByArea
member.summary: Whether the whole area or just the line should respond to mouseover tooltips and other mouse or touch events.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.TurboThreshold
member.summary: When a series contains a data array that is longer than this, only one dimensional arrays of numbers, or two dimensional arrays with x and y values are allowed. Also, only the first point is tested, and the rest are assumed to be the same format. This saves expensive data checking and indexing in long series. Set it to 0 disable.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Visible
member.summary: Set the initial visibility of the series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.ZoneAxis
member.summary: Defines the Axis on which the zones are applied.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreaspline.Zones
member.summary: An array defining zones within a series.

summary.p: Datetime formats for the header of the tooltip in a stock chart. The format can vary within a chart depending on the currently selected time range and the current data grouping.
The default formats are:

For each of these array definitions, the first item is the format used when the active time span is one unit. For instance, if the current data applies to one week, the first item of the week array is used. The second and third items are used when the active time span is more than two units. For instance, if the current data applies to two weeks, the second and third item of the week array are used, and applied to the start and end date of the time span.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataGrouping.Enabled
member.summary: Enable or disable data grouping. Defaults to true.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataGrouping.Forced
member.summary: When data grouping is forced, it runs no matter how small the intervals are. This can be handy for example when the sum should be calculated for values appearing at random times within each hour. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataGrouping.GroupPixelWidth
member.summary: The approximate pixel width of each group. If for example a series with 30 points is displayed over a 600 pixel wide plot area, no grouping is performed. If however the series contains so many points that the spacing is less than the groupPixelWidth, Highcharts will try to group it into appropriate groups so that each is more or less two pixels wide. If multiple series with different group pixel widths are drawn on the same x axis, all series will take the greatest width. For example, line series have 2px default group width, while column series have 10px. If combined, both the line and the column will have 10px by default. Defaults to 2.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataGrouping.Smoothed
member.summary: Normally, a group is indexed by the start of that group, so for example when 30 daily values are grouped into one month, that month's x value will be the 1st of the month. This apparently shifts the data to the left. When the smoothed option is true, this is compensated for. The data is shifted to the middle of the group, and min and max values are preserved. Internally, this is used in the Navigator series. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Align
member.summary: The alignment of the data label compared to the point. If right, the right side of the label should be touching the point. For points with an extent, like columns, the alignments also dictates how to align it inside the box, as given with the inside option. Can be one of "left", "center" or "right".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.AllowOverlap
member.summary: Whether to allow data labels to overlap. To make the labels less sensitive for overlapping, the dataLabels.padding can be set to 0.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.BorderColor
member.summary: The border color for the data label. Defaults to undefined.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.BorderRadius
member.summary: The border radius in pixels for the data label.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.BorderWidth
member.summary: The border width in pixels for the data label.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Color
member.summary: The text color for the data labels. Defaults to null.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Crop
member.summary: Whether to hide data labels that are outside the plot area. By default, the data label is moved inside the plot area according to the overflow option.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Defer
member.summary: Whether to defer displaying the data labels until the initial series animation has finished.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Enabled
member.summary: Enable or disable the data labels.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Format
member.summary: A format string for the data label. Available variables are the same as for formatter.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Formatter
member.summary:
Callback JavaScript function to format the data label. Note that if a format is defined, the format takes precedence and the formatter is ignored. Available data are:
this.percentage Stacked series and pies only. The point's percentage of the total.
this.point The point object. The point name, if defined, is available through this.point.name.
this.series: The series object. The series name is available through this.series.name.
this.total Stacked series only. The total value at this point's x value.
this.x: The x value.
this.y: The y value.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Inside
member.summary: For points with an extent, like columns, whether to align the data label inside the box or to the actual value point. Defaults to false in most cases, true in stacked columns.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Overflow
member.summary: How to handle data labels that flow outside the plot area. The default is justify, which aligns them inside the plot area. For columns and bars, this means it will be moved inside the bar. To display data labels outside the plot area, set crop to false and overflow to "none".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Padding
member.summary: When either the borderWidth or the backgroundColor is set, this is the padding within the box.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Rotation
member.summary: Text rotation in degrees. Note that due to a more complex structure, backgrounds, borders and padding will be lost on a rotated data label.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Shadow
member.summary: The shadow of the box. Works best with borderWidth or backgroundColor. Since 1.1.7 the shadow can be an object configuration containing color, offsetX, offsetY, opacity and width.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Shape
member.summary: The name of a symbol to use for the border around the label. Symbols are predefined functions on the Renderer object.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Style

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.UseHTML
member.summary: Whether to use HTML to render the labels.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.VerticalAlign
member.summary: The vertical alignment of a data label. Can be one of top, middle or bottom. The default value depends on the data, for instance in a column chart, the label is above positive values and below negative values.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.X
member.summary: The x position offset of the label relative to the point.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineDataLabels.Y

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineEvents.AfterAnimate
member.summary: Fires after the series has finished its initial animation, or in case animation is disabled, immediately as the series is displayed.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplineEvents.CheckboxClick
member.summary: Fires when the checkbox next to the series' name in the legend is clicked. One parameter, event, is passed to the function. The state of the checkbox is found by event.checked. summary.p: A predefined shape or symbol for the marker. When null, the symbol is pulled from options.symbols. Other possible values are "circle", "square", "diamond", "triangle" and "triangle-down".
Additionally, the URL to a graphic can be given on this form: "url(graphic.png)". Note that for the image to be applied to exported charts, its URL needs to be accessible by the export server.
Custom callbacks for symbol path generation can also be added to Highcharts.SVGRenderer.prototype.symbols. The callback is then used by its method name, as shown in the demo.

member.summary: Allow this series' points to be selected by clicking on the markers or bars.

summary.p: Enable or disable the initial animation when a series is displayed. The animation can also be set as a configuration object. Please note that this option only applies to the initial animation of the series itself. For other animations, see chart.animation and the animation parameter under the API methods.The following properties are supported:

dl.dd: The duration of the animation in milliseconds.

When using jQuery as the general framework, the easing can be set to linear orswing. More easing functions are available with the use of jQuery plug-ins, most notablythe jQuery UI suite. See the jQuery docs. When using MooTools as the general framework, use the property name transition instead of easing.

summary.p: Due to poor performance, animation is disabled in old IE browsers for column charts and polar charts.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Color
member.summary: The main color of the series. In line type series it applies to the line and the point markers unless otherwise specified. In bar type series it applies to the bars unless a color is specified per point. The default value is pulled from the options.colors array.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Compare
member.summary: Compare the values of the series against the first value in the visible range. The y axis will show percentage or absolute change depending on whether compare is set to "percent" or "value". When this is applied to multiple series, it allows comparing the development of the series against each other.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.ConnectNulls
member.summary: Whether to draw a line between points on either side of a null point, or render a gap between them.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.CropThreshold
member.summary: When the series contains less points than the crop threshold, all points are drawn, event if the points fall outside the visible plot area at the current zoom. The advantage of drawing all points (including markers and columns), is that animation is performed on updates. On the other hand, when the series contains more points than the crop threshold, the series data is cropped to only contain points that fall within the plot area. The advantage of cropping away invisible points is to increase performance on large series. .

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Cursor
member.summary: You can set the cursor to "pointer" if you have click events attached to the series, to signal to the user that the points and lines can be clicked.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.DashStyle
member.summary:
A name for the dash style to use for the graph. Applies only to series type having a graph, like line, spline, area and scatter in case it has a lineWidth. The value for the dashStyle include:
Solid
ShortDash
ShortDot
ShortDashDot
ShortDashDotDot
Dot
Dash
LongDash
DashDot
LongDashDot
LongDashDotDot

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.DataLabels
member.summary: Extended data labels for range series types. Range series data labels have no x and y options. Instead, they have xLow, xHigh, yLow and yHigh options to allow the higher and lower data label sets individually.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.EnableMouseTracking
member.summary: Enable or disable the mouse tracking for a specific series. This includes point tooltips and click events on graphs and points. When using shared tooltips (default in stock charts), mouse tracking is not required. For large datasets it improves performance.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.FillColor
member.summary: Fill color or gradient for the area. When null, the series' color is used with the series' fillOpacity.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.FillOpacity
member.summary: Fill opacity for the area. Note that when you set an explicit fillColor, the fillOpacity is not applied. Instead, you should define the opacity in the fillColor with an rgba color definition.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.GapSize
member.summary:
Defines when to display a gap in the graph. A gap size of 5 means that if the distance between two points is greater than five times that of the two closest points, the graph will be broken.
In practice, this option is most often used to visualize gaps in time series. In a stock chart, intraday data is available for daytime hours, while gaps will appear in nights and weekends..

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Keys
member.summary: An array specifying which option maps to which key in the data point array. This makes it convenient to work with unstructured data arrays from different sources.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.LegendIndex
member.summary: The sequential index of the series within the legend.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.LineColor
member.summary: A separate color for the graph line. By default the line takes the color of the series, but the lineColor setting allows setting a separate color for the line without altering the fillColor.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.LineWidth
member.summary: Pixel width of the arearange graph line.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.LinkedTo
member.summary: The id of another series to link to. Additionally, the value can be ":previous" to link to the previous series. When two series are linked, only the first one appears in the legend. Toggling the visibility of this also toggles the linked series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Point
member.summary: Properties for each single point

summary.p: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointInterval defines the interval of the x values in milliseconds. For example, if a series contains one value each day, set pointInterval to 24 * 3600 * 1000.
Since Highstock 2.1, it can be combined with pointIntervalUnit to draw irregular intervals.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.PointIntervalUnit
member.summary: On datetime series, this allows for setting the pointInterval to the two irregular time units, month and year. Combine it with pointInterval to draw quarters, 6 months, 10 years etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.PointRange
member.summary: The width of each point on the x axis. For example in a column chart with one value each day, the pointRange would be 1 day (= 24 * 3600 * 1000 milliseconds). This is normally computed automatically, but this option can be used to override the automatic value.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.PointStart
member.summary: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointStart defines on what value to start. On a datetime X axis, the number will be given as milliseconds since 1970-01-01, for example Date.UTC(2011, 0, 1).

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Selected
member.summary: Whether to select the series initially. If showCheckbox is true, the checkbox next to the series name in the legend will be checked for a selected series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Shadow
member.summary: Whether to apply a drop shadow to the graph line. Since 1.1.7 the shadow can be an object configuration containing color, offsetX, offsetY, opacity and width.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.ShowCheckbox
member.summary: If true, a checkbox is displayed next to the legend item to allow selecting the series. The state of the checkbox is determined by the selected option.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.ShowInLegend
member.summary: Whether to display this particular series or series type in the legend. The default value is true for standalone series, false for linked series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Stacking
member.summary: Whether to stack the values of each series on top of each other. Possible values are null to disable, "normal" to stack by value or "percent".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.States
member.summary: A wrapper object for all the series options in specific states.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.StickyTracking
member.summary: Sticky tracking of mouse events. When true, the mouseOut event on a series isn't triggered until the mouse moves over another series, or out of the plot area. When false, the mouseOut event on a series is triggered when the mouse leaves the area around the series' graph or markers. This also implies the tooltip when not shared. When stickyTracking is false, the tooltip will be hidden when moving the mouse between series. Defaults to true for line and area type series, but to false for columns, candlesticks etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Tooltip
member.summary: A configuration object for the tooltip rendering of each single series. Properties are inherited from tooltip, but only the following properties can be defined on a series level.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.TrackByArea
member.summary: Whether the whole area or just the line should respond to mouseover tooltips and other mouse or touch events.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.TurboThreshold
member.summary: When a series contains a data array that is longer than this, only one dimensional arrays of numbers, or two dimensional arrays with x and y values are allowed. Also, only the first point is tested, and the rest are assumed to be the same format. This saves expensive data checking and indexing in long series. Set it to 0 disable.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Visible
member.summary: Set the initial visibility of the series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.ZoneAxis
member.summary: Defines the Axis on which the zones are applied.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerange.Zones
member.summary: An array defining zones within a series.

summary.p: Datetime formats for the header of the tooltip in a stock chart. The format can vary within a chart depending on the currently selected time range and the current data grouping.
The default formats are:

For each of these array definitions, the first item is the format used when the active time span is one unit. For instance, if the current data applies to one week, the first item of the week array is used. The second and third items are used when the active time span is more than two units. For instance, if the current data applies to two weeks, the second and third item of the week array are used, and applied to the start and end date of the time span.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataGrouping.Enabled
member.summary: Enable or disable data grouping. Defaults to true.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataGrouping.Forced
member.summary: When data grouping is forced, it runs no matter how small the intervals are. This can be handy for example when the sum should be calculated for values appearing at random times within each hour. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataGrouping.GroupPixelWidth
member.summary: The approximate pixel width of each group. If for example a series with 30 points is displayed over a 600 pixel wide plot area, no grouping is performed. If however the series contains so many points that the spacing is less than the groupPixelWidth, Highcharts will try to group it into appropriate groups so that each is more or less two pixels wide. If multiple series with different group pixel widths are drawn on the same x axis, all series will take the greatest width. For example, line series have 2px default group width, while column series have 10px. If combined, both the line and the column will have 10px by default. Defaults to 2.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataGrouping.Smoothed
member.summary: Normally, a group is indexed by the start of that group, so for example when 30 daily values are grouped into one month, that month's x value will be the 1st of the month. This apparently shifts the data to the left. When the smoothed option is true, this is compensated for. The data is shifted to the middle of the group, and min and max values are preserved. Internally, this is used in the Navigator series. Defaults to false.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataLabels.Align
member.summary: The alignment of the data label compared to the point. If right, the right side of the label should be touching the point. For points with an extent, like columns, the alignments also dictates how to align it inside the box, as given with the inside option. Can be one of "left", "center" or "right".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataLabels.AllowOverlap
member.summary: Whether to allow data labels to overlap. To make the labels less sensitive for overlapping, the dataLabels.padding can be set to 0.

member.summary: A format string for the data label. Available variables are the same as for formatter.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataLabels.Formatter
member.summary:
Callback JavaScript function to format the data label. Note that if a format is defined, the format takes precedence and the formatter is ignored. Available data are:
this.percentage Stacked series and pies only. The point's percentage of the total.
this.point The point object. The point name, if defined, is available through this.point.name.
this.series: The series object. The series name is available through this.series.name.
this.total Stacked series only. The total value at this point's x value.
this.x: The x value.
this.y: The y value.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataLabels.Inside

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataLabels.Overflow
member.summary: How to handle data labels that flow outside the plot area. The default is justify, which aligns them inside the plot area. For columns and bars, this means it will be moved inside the bar. To display data labels outside the plot area, set crop to false and overflow to "none".

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeDataLabels.Padding

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsAreasplinerangeTooltip.FollowTouchMove
member.summary: Whether the tooltip should follow the finger as it moves on a touch device. In order to take effect, chart.zoomType and chart.pinchType must be disabled.

summary.p: The HTML of the tooltip header line. Variables are enclosed by curly brackets. Available variablesare point.key, series.name, series.color and other members from the point and series objects. The point.key variable contains the category name, x value or datetime string depending on the type of axis. For datetime axes, the point.key date format can be set using tooltip.xDateFormat.
Defaults to {point.key}

The HTML of the point's line in the tooltip. Variables are enclosed by curly brackets. Available variables are point.x, point.y, point.change, series.name and series.color and other properties on the same form. Furthermore, point.y can be extended by the tooltip.valuePrefix and tooltip.valueSuffix variables. This can also be overridden for each series, which makes it a good hook for displaying units.

member.summary: Allow this series' points to be selected by clicking on the markers or bars.

summary.p: Enable or disable the initial animation when a series is displayed. The animation can also be set as a configuration object. Please note that this option only applies to the initial animation of the series itself. For other animations, see chart.animation and the animation parameter under the API methods.The following properties are supported:

dl.dd: The duration of the animation in milliseconds.

When using jQuery as the general framework, the easing can be set to linear orswing. More easing functions are available with the use of jQuery plug-ins, most notablythe jQuery UI suite. See the jQuery docs. When using MooTools as the general framework, use the property name transition instead of easing.

summary.p: Due to poor performance, animation is disabled in old IE browsers for column charts and polar charts.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.Color
member.summary: The main color of the series. In line type series it applies to the line and the point markers unless otherwise specified. In bar type series it applies to the bars unless a color is specified per point. The default value is pulled from the options.colors array.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.Colors
member.summary: A series specific or series type specific color set to apply instead of the global colors when colorByPoint is true.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.CropThreshold
member.summary: When the series contains less points than the crop threshold, all points are drawn, event if the points fall outside the visible plot area at the current zoom. The advantage of drawing all points (including markers and columns), is that animation is performed on updates. On the other hand, when the series contains more points than the crop threshold, the series data is cropped to only contain points that fall within the plot area. The advantage of cropping away invisible points is to increase performance on large series. .

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.Cursor
member.summary: You can set the cursor to "pointer" if you have click events attached to the series, to signal to the user that the points and lines can be clicked.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.EnableMouseTracking
member.summary: Enable or disable the mouse tracking for a specific series. This includes point tooltips and click events on graphs and points. When using shared tooltips (default in stock charts), mouse tracking is not required. For large datasets it improves performance.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.GroupPadding
member.summary: Padding between each value groups, in x axis units.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.Grouping
member.summary: Whether to group non-stacked columns or to let them render independent of each other. Non-grouped columns will be laid out individually and overlap each other.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.Keys
member.summary: An array specifying which option maps to which key in the data point array. This makes it convenient to work with unstructured data arrays from different sources.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.LegendIndex
member.summary: The sequential index of the series within the legend.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.LineColor
member.summary: The color of the line/border of the candlestick.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.LineWidth
member.summary: The pixel width of the candlestick line/border. Defaults to 1.

member.summary: The minimal height for a column or width for a bar. By default, 0 values are not shown. To visualize a 0 (or close to zero) point, set the minimal point length to a pixel value like 3. In stacked column charts, minPointLength might not be respected for tightly packed values.

summary.p: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointInterval defines the interval of the x values in milliseconds. For example, if a series contains one value each day, set pointInterval to 24 * 3600 * 1000.
Since Highstock 2.1, it can be combined with pointIntervalUnit to draw irregular intervals.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.PointIntervalUnit
member.summary: On datetime series, this allows for setting the pointInterval to the two irregular time units, month and year. Combine it with pointInterval to draw quarters, 6 months, 10 years etc.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.PointPadding
member.summary: Padding between each column or bar, in x axis units.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.PointRange
member.summary: The width of each point on the x axis. For example in a column chart with one value each day, the pointRange would be 1 day (= 24 * 3600 * 1000 milliseconds). This is normally computed automatically, but this option can be used to override the automatic value. In a series on a categorized axis the pointRange is 1 by default.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.PointStart
member.summary: If no x values are given for the points in a series, pointStart defines on what value to start. On a datetime X axis, the number will be given as milliseconds since 1970-01-01, for example Date.UTC(2011, 0, 1).

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.PointWidth
member.summary: A pixel value specifying a fixed width for each column or bar. When null, the width is calculated from the pointPadding and groupPadding.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.Selected

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.Shadow
member.summary: Whether to apply a drop shadow to the graph line. Since 1.1.7 the shadow can be an object configuration containing color, offsetX, offsetY, opacity and width.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.ShowCheckbox

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.ShowInLegend
member.summary: Whether to display this particular series or series type in the legend. The default value is true for standalone series, false for linked series.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.States
member.summary: A wrapper object for all the series options in specific states.

member.name: P:Highsoft.Web.Mvc.Stocks.PlotOptionsCandlestick.StickyTracking
member.summary: Sticky tracking of mouse events. When true, the mouseOut event on a series isn't triggered until the mouse moves over another series, or out of the plot area. When false, the mouseOut event on a series is triggered when the mouse leaves the area around the series' graph or markers. This also implies the tooltip when not shared. When stickyTracking is false, the tooltip will be hidden when moving the mouse between series. Defaults to true for line and area type series, but to false for columns, candlesticks etc.

member.summary: When a series contains a data array that is longer than this, only one dimensional arrays of numbers, or two dimensional arrays with x and y values are allowed. Also, only the first point is tested, and the rest are assumed to be the same format. This saves expensive data checking and indexing in long series. Set it to 0 disable.
